\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 Real progress is growth. It must begin in the seed. Then, \'93first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear.\'94 There is something to encourage and inspire us in the advancement of individuals since their emancipation from slavery. It at least proves that there is nothing irretrievably wrong in the shape of the black man\'92s skull, and that under given circumstances his development, downward or upward, will be similar to that of other average human beings.\
