\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 pleased God to call them. True, like the old professor lecturing to his solitary student, we make no provision here for irregularities. \'93Questions must be kept till after class,\'94 or dispensed with altogether. That some do ask questions and insist on answers, in class too, must be both impertinent and annoying. Let not our spiritual pastors and masters however be grieved at such self-assertion as merely signifies we have a destiny to fulfill and as men and women we must\'a0
