\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 That our people are not \'93drawn\'94 to a church whose chief dignitaries they see only in the chancel, and whom they reverence as they would a painting or an angel, whose life never comes down to and touches theirs with the inspiration of an objective reality, may be \'93perplexing\'94 truly (American caste and American Christianity both being facts) but it need not be surprising. There must be something of human nature in it, the same as that which brought about that \'93the Word was made flesh and dwelt among us\'94 that He might \'93draw\'94 us towards God.\
