Then too we need the calm clear judgment of ourselves and of others born of a disenchantment similar to that of a little girl I know in the South, who was once being laboriously held up over the shoulders of a surging throng to catch her first glimpse of a real live president. \'93Why Nunny,\'94 she cried half reproachfully, as she strained her little neck to see\'97\'93
\f1\i It\'92s nuffin but a man!
\f0\i0 \'94\
When we have been sized up and written down by others, we need not feel that the last word is said and the oracles sealed. \'93It\'92s nuffin but a man.\'94 And there are many gifts the giftie may gie us, far better than seeing\'a0
